text: George Herrick Worker was born 23 August, 1989 in Palmerston North. He was a New Zealand cricketer who played 10 one-day internationals, 2 twenty20 internationals and no tests for New Zealand. He also played for Canterbury, Central Districts and Auckland in the Plunket Shield. He was related to Rupert Worker. ==Other websites== * Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand cricketers Category:People from Palmerston North
